The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 October is 79,125 (9,119.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 October, there were 2,533 new confirmed cases (291.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 September, there were 2,298 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 10% (235 extra cases).
